# .env.example
# -------------
# Environment variables are the safest place for SECRETS (like API keys),
# because this file's real version (.env) is ignored by git.
#
# To use it:
#   1. Copy this file to .env      ->   cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in the values you need.
#
# Naming rule: every variable starts with NOVA_ , and a DOUBLE underscore (__)
# separates the section from the setting. These OVERRIDE config.yaml.

# --- Cloud AI (Anthropic Claude) ---
# Only needed if you set the AI provider to "anthropic". Nova's default provider
# is "ollama" (fully local), so you can leave this blank and Nova runs offline.
#
# This is a STANDARD, pay-as-you-go Anthropic API key (it starts with "sk-ant-").
# Get it from https://console.anthropic.com/ ; it is billed via API credits.
# It is COMPLETELY INDEPENDENT of any Claude subscription (Claude Max / Pro) and of
# the Claude Code CLI — canceling those does NOT affect Nova. Nova calls the
# Anthropic API directly with this key; it never shells out to the `claude` command.
# NOVA_AI__ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# --- Examples of overriding other settings (all optional) ---
# NOVA_AI__PROVIDER=anthropic
# NOVA_SERVER__PORT=9000
# NOVA_LOGGING__LEVEL=DEBUG

# --- Point Nova at a different config file (optional) ---
# NOVA_CONFIG_FILE=config/config.yaml
